CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 5, 1946, pg. 8 reads: "Double Ring Ceremony - Charming Miss Rosetta Austin, daughter of Edward Austin Sr., was united in marriage Sept. 24 with Hardine Moore, son of Mrs. Hardine Moore of Lynchburg, Va., in a ceremony held in home of Mr. and Mrs. George Austin. The Rev. J.B. Campbell officiated. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Austin - Moore wedding party with seven men and six women, including groom Hardine Moore, center, next to bride Rosetta Austin Moore, posed in home of Mr. and Mrs. George Austin with stenciled walls
